01:05:08.000 --> 01:05:10.753
Shit!

01:05:13.040 --> 01:05:17.079
Hey, lighten up, little brother!

01:05:18.560 --> 01:05:22.838
- This ain't no time to get funky, man.
- I ain't shit.

01:05:23.000 --> 01:05:24.991
Now, be with this.

01:05:27.000 --> 01:05:29.560
I read the paper today, man,

01:05:29.720 --> 01:05:33.156
and the union,
they're ready to pay the bread.

01:05:34.800 --> 01:05:36.950
We gonna be rich, man!

01:05:40.160 --> 01:05:43.596
Let's settle down.
You boys take a seat.

01:05:43.760 --> 01:05:47.594
The whole thing, they're going to pay
the whole ten grand?

01:05:49.080 --> 01:05:51.036
I've never seen that much money.

01:05:51.200 --> 01:05:53.668
That's over $3,000 apiece, at one time.

01:05:56.440 --> 01:05:58.351
I don't think we better sit together.

01:05:58.520 --> 01:06:00.556
All right, let's settle down.

01:06:00.720 --> 01:06:03.473
You boys, come in and take a seat
so we can get started.

01:06:03.640 --> 01:06:05.790
How much
money was there, Clarence?

01:06:05.960 --> 01:06:08.394
Well, there was a little over $20,000.

01:06:08.560 --> 01:06:13.429
- $20,600, to be exact.
- Wait a minute, $20,000?

01:06:13.600 --> 01:06:15.875
What's the union doing
with so much cash?

01:06:16.040 --> 01:06:19.919
We were just holding it temporarily.
It's for local 644's strike fund.

01:06:20.080 --> 01:06:21.798
Somebody must have known.

01:06:21.960 --> 01:06:25.555
Why don't you protect your money?
The papers said the safe was open!

01:06:25.720 --> 01:06:29.759
- Now, that's not exactly right.
- All right, sit down.

01:06:30.840 --> 01:06:34.719
It wasn't our money.
It was your money.

01:06:34.880 --> 01:06:37.155
They stole your money!

01:06:37.320 --> 01:06:40.437
Now you're talking.
How we gonna get our money back?

01:06:40.600 --> 01:06:42.352
Well, it was insured.

01:06:42.520 --> 01:06:45.114
Insured?
What about the dudes that did it?

01:06:45.280 --> 01:06:47.840
Well, the cops'll find 'em.

01:06:48.000 --> 01:06:51.356
Police Department owes
this union some favours.

01:06:51.520 --> 01:06:55.229
We're standing outside
the AAW local 291 union hall.

01:06:55.400 --> 01:06:58.790
We see them coming out now,
and perhaps we can talk to one or two.

01:06:58.960 --> 01:07:01.758
Find out what they know.
Here's a man. Pardon me, sir.

01:07:01.920 --> 01:07:03.956
- Get the fuck out of here.
- Thank you.

01:07:04.120 --> 01:07:06.634
Perhaps we can get another opinion. Sir?

01:07:06.800 --> 01:07:10.236
Son of a bitch. Shit, I don't know.

01:07:10.400 --> 01:07:13.278
I'll tell you something.
We're the workers at the plant.

01:07:13.440 --> 01:07:16.512
The managers are just there
to oversee us, you know...

01:07:16.680 --> 01:07:20.832
You know something? I think we gotta
start talking about that switch.

01:07:21.000 --> 01:07:23.560
You know what I mean?

01:07:23.720 --> 01:07:26.280
Let's go to the bar.

01:07:31.240 --> 01:07:32.912
- Jesus!
- No, no, no.

01:07:33.080 --> 01:07:36.868
- Who is he?
- My name's Charlie T Hernandez.

01:07:37.040 --> 01:07:39.349
- Smokey knows who I am.
- Right.

01:07:39.520 --> 01:07:42.876
- You owe me some money.
- Look, Charlie.

01:07:43.040 --> 01:07:46.191
Don't believe any of that shit
you read in the papers.

01:07:46.360 --> 01:07:49.079
This is just an insurance scam
created by the union.

01:07:49.240 --> 01:07:51.037
I don't want to hear no stories.

01:07:51.200 --> 01:07:54.909
- I just want my grand.
- But man, we've got something else!

01:07:55.080 --> 01:07:57.435
Stuff that the union
will pay money for.

01:07:57.600 --> 01:07:59.352
Then you'll get your grand.

01:07:59.520 --> 01:08:02.159
Yeah, just give us
a couple of weeks, man.

01:08:02.320 --> 01:08:04.231
What kind of stuff?

01:08:04.400 --> 01:08:07.631
- Illegal loan lists...
- Just stuff, bullshit, Charlie.

01:08:07.800 --> 01:08:09.995
I would tell you if it wasn't bullshit.

01:08:10.800 --> 01:08:12.711
OK.

01:08:12.880 --> 01:08:16.395
Smoke and me go way back,
so I'll give you a couple of weeks.

01:08:16.560 --> 01:08:19.313
Smoke always pays his bills.

01:08:20.399 --> 01:08:23.596
Charlie, the union said
they're gonna give us the money,

01:08:23.760 --> 01:08:26.638
but I mean, like, what if they don't?

01:08:26.800 --> 01:08:30.917
You'll find it. You'll find it
even if you gotta sell this car.

01:08:31.080 --> 01:08:33.674
You know that, don't you, Smoke?

01:08:35.120 --> 01:08:38.669
Yeah, I know that, Charlie.

01:09:08.319 --> 01:09:12.198
I can't believe the union
raised the insurance claim $10,000.

01:09:12.359 --> 01:09:14.953
- I don't fucking believe it.
- That's $20,000.

01:09:15.120 --> 01:09:17.839
They're gonna pay us ten
and then make ten. Fuck 'em.

01:09:18.000 --> 01:09:21.993
We ought to charge 'em the same amount
they charging the insurance company.

01:09:22.160 --> 01:09:25.118
- Playing softball, Jerry?
- Yeah, 9:00.

01:09:26.520 --> 01:09:30.035
This thing, man, is turning into...

01:09:30.200 --> 01:09:32.953
- How're we gonna get the bread?
- I don't know, man.

01:09:33.120 --> 01:09:35.031
I thought you had it all figured out.

01:09:35.200 --> 01:09:36.952
What am I, a fucking genius?

01:09:37.120 --> 01:09:40.635
You know how difficult it is
to make a fucking switch?

01:09:40.800 --> 01:09:42.870
Could we get a locker
at the bus station?

01:09:43.040 --> 01:09:46.715
- They'll spot us hauling the bread.
- Not if they're afraid of the book.

01:09:46.880 --> 01:09:50.872
That's one thing we gotta think about.
How badly do they want that book?

01:09:51.040 --> 01:09:54.191
This is what we gotta figure,
you know what I mean?

01:09:54.360 --> 01:09:56.112
Tear the book up in half.

01:09:56.280 --> 01:10:00.831
We give them half, and when they give us
the money, we give 'em the other half.

01:10:10.840 --> 01:10:12.751
This ain't gonna fucking work, man.

01:10:12.920 --> 01:10:16.435
Smokey, it'll work.
We can get a post-office-box key.

01:10:16.600 --> 01:10:20.639
This ain't what I'm talking about, Zeke.
We can't be seen with each other.

01:10:20.800 --> 01:10:24.395
They know three guys did it,
two of them black, one white.

01:10:27.640 --> 01:10:31.110
- So what?
- We can't be seen with each other.

01:10:31.280 --> 01:10:33.589
We gotta talk by phone from now on.

01:10:33.760 --> 01:10:36.399
It's dangerous,
hanging out with each other.

01:10:36.560 --> 01:10:38.755
We can't do this, understand me?

01:10:38.920 --> 01:10:42.037
If anybody asks,
we never hung out with each other.

01:10:42.200 --> 01:10:45.317
This is the end.
We gotta go our own way now.

01:10:51.280 --> 01:10:53.157
That's too bad.

01:10:55.360 --> 01:10:58.352
Arlene's gonna miss the bowling.

01:10:58.520 --> 01:11:01.034
Shit, she couldn't bowl, no how.

01:11:05.160 --> 01:11:07.230
Well, take care, man.

01:11:14.720 --> 01:11:17.075
Fuck.

01:11:17.240 --> 01:11:22.394
Hey, wanna beer?
Wanna beer? Fuck fate.

01:11:23.600 --> 01:11:25.795
Take it easy.

01:11:52.280 --> 01:11:55.113
I think you made a mistake, Hernandez.

01:11:55.280 --> 01:11:59.034
We found a Harrington
and Richardson.32 in the hall.

01:11:59.200 --> 01:12:04.228
Ballistics said it was the gun that shot
a police officer three weeks ago.

01:12:04.400 --> 01:12:06.197
He's still in the hospital.

01:12:07.520 --> 01:12:11.991
Hey, man, you know I wouldn't have
anything to do with a shooting.

01:12:12.160 --> 01:12:14.310
Do we?

01:12:16.040 --> 01:12:18.838
OK, so it don't look good. All right.

01:12:20.840 --> 01:12:23.274
What can I trade?

01:12:23.440 --> 01:12:27.513
- What do you want to know?
- Whatcha got?

01:12:27.680 --> 01:12:31.355
- I got three nobodies.
- So?

01:12:31.520 --> 01:12:35.638
So, three nobodies got caught in
something bigger than they can handle.

01:12:35.800 --> 01:12:37.916
Union stuff.

01:12:38.080 --> 01:12:41.789
Something so big
you'll have to hush it up.

01:12:43.080 --> 01:12:45.469
This one's a union man.

01:12:45.640 --> 01:12:47.949
He'll buckle under a little pressure.

01:12:52.720 --> 01:12:56.076
Now, this one, he's hungry.

01:12:56.240 --> 01:12:59.152
He wants to get his hands
on the controls.

01:13:02.160 --> 01:13:04.913
Now, this bastard is a two-time loser.

01:13:05.080 --> 01:13:09.631
He'll make us pay through the ass
forever then fuck us for the fun of it.

01:13:09.800 --> 01:13:12.439
- Here, Smoke.
- Thank you.

01:13:23.480 --> 01:13:25.789
Well, my daddy said,
when I was little,

01:13:25.960 --> 01:13:29.236
"When you get big, work hard
so the foreman can't say nothing."

01:13:29.400 --> 01:13:31.755
"But, don't sweat."

01:13:31.920 --> 01:13:34.639
How you gonna do it without sweat?

01:13:38.640 --> 01:13:41.438
- Beer?
- And a Scotch.

01:13:41.600 --> 01:13:44.990
- Two beers and a Scotch straight up.
- Straight up?

01:13:53.040 --> 01:13:56.555
- Where's the john?
- In the rear. Use my name.

01:13:56.720 --> 01:13:58.756
Yeah, you'll get a good seat.

01:14:01.840 --> 01:14:05.389
Hello. Mrs Bartowski?
This is telephone repair service.

01:14:05.560 --> 01:14:07.790
Is your husband at home?

01:14:09.280 --> 01:14:11.999
Have you had a problem with your line?

01:14:12.160 --> 01:14:15.436
