01:15:04.040 --> 01:15:08.238
Hi. Arlene, did you just
get a telephone call?

01:15:08.400 --> 01:15:11.358
<i>Yeah, from the phone company</i>.
<i>They made a mistake</i>.

01:15:11.520 --> 01:15:14.990
Yeah, I know, I was trying to get you
and your line was busy.

01:15:16.040 --> 01:15:19.749
What do I hear, the kids in the back?
Are the kids at home, Arlene?

01:15:19.920 --> 01:15:23.708
- <i>No, why?</i>
- Oh, nothing.

01:15:23.880 --> 01:15:28.954
Jerry asked me to call. He's split
his pants down at the station house,

01:15:29.120 --> 01:15:32.476
and he wants you
to bring down an extra pair for him.

01:15:32.640 --> 01:15:35.950
- <i>Oh, OK</i>.
- OK? He's kind of embarrassed.

01:15:36.120 --> 01:15:37.838
How are you doing? You all right?

01:15:38.000 --> 01:15:40.434
- <i>I'm fine</i>.
- Good. Well, I'll see you around.

01:15:40.600 --> 01:15:43.592
<i>- OK</i>.
- OK.

01:16:26.440 --> 01:16:28.635
Mrs Bartowski?

01:16:49.280 --> 01:16:51.430
You giris looking for somebody?

01:16:51.600 --> 01:16:54.068
I think we just got the wrong house.

01:16:54.240 --> 01:16:58.916
No, man. You didn't get the wrong
house, you just got the wrong time.

01:16:59.080 --> 01:17:02.072
- We wasn't gonna do nothing.
- Lying son of a bitch!

01:17:09.000 --> 01:17:11.434
Wait a minute, man.
Come on, let's talk.

01:17:11.600 --> 01:17:14.273
- I want to know who sent you.
- Nobody!

01:17:14.440 --> 01:17:16.749
- Who sent you?
- We got the wrong house!

01:17:16.920 --> 01:17:19.673
Don't give me that fuckin' shit.

01:17:21.440 --> 01:17:25.877
Tell me who the fuck sent you. You gonna
tell me what I want to know, man?

01:17:26.040 --> 01:17:29.749
You motherfucking coon, I'll kill you!

01:17:41.760 --> 01:17:44.911
- I'm running out of patience.
- No more, brother, no more.

01:17:45.080 --> 01:17:47.036
Fuck you mean,
"No more, brother"?

01:17:47.200 --> 01:17:50.749
I want to know who sent you, man.
Gimme a name.

01:17:50.920 --> 01:17:53.957
You know he's not gonna walk no more.

01:17:54.120 --> 01:17:56.315
Who sent you?
Who sent you, man?

01:17:56.480 --> 01:17:59.233
- Who the fuck sent you?
- Some union guy, I don't...

01:17:59.400 --> 01:18:02.312
What fucking guy?
Who the fuck sent you, man?

01:18:02.480 --> 01:18:06.598
It was some guy who runs for...
for Eddie Knuckles. For Eddie Knuckles.

01:18:09.440 --> 01:18:12.796
Eddie Knuckles. Well,
that's name enough, isn't it, man?

01:18:20.120 --> 01:18:23.112
I've been watching you
for some time, Zeke.

01:18:23.280 --> 01:18:25.555
You remind me of me when I was young.

01:18:25.720 --> 01:18:30.669
A little rough, a little pushy,
you talk too much, but you got guts.

01:18:30.840 --> 01:18:34.276
Just the right kind of guy to stand up
for the working man's rights.

01:18:34.440 --> 01:18:39.878
We've thought about what you and some
of the others said about Clarence Hill.

01:18:40.040 --> 01:18:42.315
We think you're right.

01:18:42.480 --> 01:18:47.474
So Clarence Hill's going to be
transferred to a new plant in Ohio.

01:18:47.640 --> 01:18:51.838
And I'd like you to fill in for him
till the next election.

01:18:52.000 --> 01:18:55.117
The job pays $17,400 a year.

01:18:55.280 --> 01:18:58.875
Can we cut the bullshit?

01:18:59.040 --> 01:19:01.759
It's about time.

01:19:01.920 --> 01:19:05.993
I hear you got something I want.

01:19:06.160 --> 01:19:11.996
Yeah, but I want assurances that
nothing will happen to Jerry or Smokey.

01:19:12.160 --> 01:19:16.915
Course. They're union men. We'll
protect their life and their safety.

01:19:17.080 --> 01:19:19.435
Don't con me. I want your word.

01:19:19.600 --> 01:19:21.955
Well, you've got it.

01:19:22.120 --> 01:19:25.430
Are you still interested
in that rep job?

01:19:26.480 --> 01:19:29.870
I wanna be able
to make some changes.

01:19:30.040 --> 01:19:32.395
How much power am I gonna have?

01:19:32.560 --> 01:19:35.757
- How much can you handle?
- All you got.

01:19:35.920 --> 01:19:38.354
Then you have it.

01:19:38.520 --> 01:19:41.034
Now this is for real.

01:19:41.200 --> 01:19:43.794
This is a hard-ass outfit.
We don't take slackers.

01:19:43.960 --> 01:19:46.235
I ain't no slacker.

01:19:47.280 --> 01:19:49.271
Good.

01:19:55.080 --> 01:19:58.709
Utility man! Where's that fuckin' horse?

01:19:59.680 --> 01:20:02.717
Utility man! Utility man!

01:20:03.640 --> 01:20:06.029
Utility man! Utility ma...

01:20:06.200 --> 01:20:11.149
Hey, Smokey, the super says he needs
a utility man down in paint room three.

01:20:11.320 --> 01:20:15.950
Something about a car being fucked up,
and he wants you to fix it. OK?

01:20:16.120 --> 01:20:18.156
- I can be with it.
- Thank you.

01:20:24.560 --> 01:20:29.111
Zeke, them cocksuckers
came into my fuckin' house!

01:20:30.640 --> 01:20:32.915
What's gonna happen?
I'm getting scared.

01:20:33.080 --> 01:20:36.914
Will you shut the fuck up, man?
Ain't nothin' to worry about, OK?

01:20:37.080 --> 01:20:40.311
They didn't come to your fuckin' house,
they came to mine.

01:20:40.480 --> 01:20:44.519
Charlie T's been cooled out.
We don't have to go to the cops no more.

01:20:46.280 --> 01:20:48.589
What are we going to do
about the notebook?

01:20:48.760 --> 01:20:50.751
Jerry...

01:20:52.840 --> 01:20:55.832
I'll take care of it.
We'll talk about it later.

01:21:02.880 --> 01:21:05.872
What are we gonna do about it now?
That is the question.

01:21:07.400 --> 01:21:10.198
Take it easy.
We'll talk about it later tonight.

01:21:11.240 --> 01:21:13.276
- OK?
- Later.

01:21:19.760 --> 01:21:22.399
You mean he's the one
that's gonna take your place?

01:21:22.560 --> 01:21:26.269
- Zeke is gonna be the steward?
- I don't want to talk about it.

01:21:26.440 --> 01:21:29.830
That's just the way things go down.

01:23:14.680 --> 01:23:16.238
Hey, who the f...

01:23:16.400 --> 01:23:18.470
Who the...

01:23:18.640 --> 01:23:21.279
Who left that lift out there?

01:23:24.120 --> 01:23:26.111
Let me out of here!

01:26:29.600 --> 01:26:31.591
Zeke?

01:26:33.720 --> 01:26:36.951
- You motherfuckers lied to me.
- Huh?

01:26:37.120 --> 01:26:39.873
You said Smokey and Jerry would be OK.

01:26:40.040 --> 01:26:42.031
What the hell are you talking about?

01:26:42.200 --> 01:26:45.829
I'm talking about Smokey.
I'm talking about his death!

01:26:47.400 --> 01:26:50.437
We've been having meetings all morning.

01:26:50.600 --> 01:26:54.513
And we found out that James' death
was the result of negligence

01:26:54.680 --> 01:26:57.114
and improper safety precautions.

01:26:57.280 --> 01:26:59.236
Fuck that, man! You had him murdered!

01:27:00.760 --> 01:27:04.070
You be damn careful
who you call a murderer, Zeke.

01:27:04.240 --> 01:27:07.312
What in the fuck do you call it, Eddie?

01:27:07.480 --> 01:27:11.678
I'm going to give you a quick education,
son, and you better listen good.

01:27:13.080 --> 01:27:17.073
When I was your age, there were no
blacks working in the auto plants.

01:27:17.240 --> 01:27:19.071
- No blacks...
- Eddie...

01:27:19.240 --> 01:27:24.837
Blacks gotjobs because guys like me
knew when to stand up...

01:27:25.000 --> 01:27:28.037
and when to look the other way.

01:27:28.200 --> 01:27:32.910
I coulda talked to Smokey. I coulda
fixed it if you'd gave me a chance!

01:27:33.080 --> 01:27:34.991
You didn't have to have him killed!

01:27:35.160 --> 01:27:37.628
Now, come on, Zeke, wake up, will you?

01:27:39.400 --> 01:27:42.517
How the hell do you think
things get changed around here?

01:27:42.680 --> 01:27:45.353
Not by pie-in-the-sky martyrs!

01:27:46.360 --> 01:27:48.828
Nothing's gonna happen to you, Zeke.

01:27:49.000 --> 01:27:52.788
You just thought that
being a union rep was going to be easy.

01:27:52.960 --> 01:27:58.478
Now you know, it's tough and it's rough.

01:27:58.640 --> 01:28:01.552
You know, I thought you had guts.

