That was this fall.
We didn't go. You changed your mind.

01:29:00.080 --> 01:29:04.631
I been thinking about it.
Maybe you ought to go. Take the kids.

01:29:04.800 --> 01:29:07.678
What are you talking about?
The kids are in school.

01:29:10.120 --> 01:29:12.759
I want you and the kids
to get out of town.

01:29:12.920 --> 01:29:15.275
You'll take the Greyhound
in the morning.

01:29:15.440 --> 01:29:16.759
Jerry, what's going on?

01:29:16.920 --> 01:29:21.357
Something funny with the union.
I don't think you should be here.

01:29:21.520 --> 01:29:25.798
Does this have anything to do with
Smokey James's death?

01:29:25.960 --> 01:29:27.632
Yeah.

01:29:35.240 --> 01:29:38.391
Listen, Zeke, we both know
Smokey was murdered.

01:29:38.560 --> 01:29:41.597
It wasn't no fucking accident
like the company says.

01:29:43.080 --> 01:29:45.230
What are we going to do about it?

01:29:47.240 --> 01:29:49.834
Nothin'.

01:29:50.000 --> 01:29:52.116
Nothing can help Smokey now.

01:29:52.280 --> 01:29:54.236
Our friend's been killed, Zeke.

01:29:54.400 --> 01:29:57.233
We have to expose the union,
like you said.

01:29:57.400 --> 01:30:01.552
- It's not that simple, man.
- What do you mean?

01:30:01.720 --> 01:30:05.315
We can't expose the union
without going to jail ourselves.

01:30:05.480 --> 01:30:09.189
Maybe we can make
some kind of deal with the FBI guy.

01:30:09.360 --> 01:30:11.351
What's his name? Burrows.

01:30:13.600 --> 01:30:15.830
How're we gonna live to tell about it?

01:30:16.000 --> 01:30:20.391
- What about the notebook?
- Things have gotten complicated.

01:30:20.560 --> 01:30:25.680
- It is not that simple anymore.
- You mean, you don't have the notebook?

01:30:25.840 --> 01:30:31.198
I mean there's gonna be some changes
in the union. Big changes.

01:30:32.880 --> 01:30:35.394
I'm taking over Clarence Hill's job.

01:30:35.560 --> 01:30:38.120
I'm gonna be the new shop steward.

01:30:40.360 --> 01:30:42.351
Jesus.

01:30:45.440 --> 01:30:47.954
You gave it to them.

01:30:48.120 --> 01:30:50.634
Dennis, get your ass out of the street.

01:30:50.800 --> 01:30:52.153
We're playing, Dad.

01:30:52.320 --> 01:30:55.039
I don't give a fuck.
Get outta the street.

01:30:58.560 --> 01:31:00.915
It wasn't illegal anyway, man.

01:31:01.080 --> 01:31:04.516
Well, illegal, but not illegal
in the sense that we know.

01:31:04.680 --> 01:31:10.038
It's big business, man. The union loans
money to people in Vegas and New York.

01:31:10.200 --> 01:31:14.432
They charge a high interest rate.
Never miss one payment.

01:31:14.600 --> 01:31:17.034
That's how it's done, man.

01:31:20.280 --> 01:31:26.719
You dumb asshole. You think those
bastards will let you change anything?

01:31:26.880 --> 01:31:29.997
They just bought you off
with a promotion.

01:31:30.160 --> 01:31:32.754
No, they think they bought
me off with a promotion.

01:31:32.920 --> 01:31:36.833
What they bought is a stick of dynamite.
I'm gonna raise hell.

01:31:37.000 --> 01:31:39.230
What about Smokey?

01:31:39.400 --> 01:31:42.073
Dogshit Miller's gonna be fired
for negligence.

01:31:43.480 --> 01:31:45.994
That don't mean shit!

01:31:46.920 --> 01:31:51.630
Man, who in the fuck are you kidding?
This is fuckin' for real.

01:31:51.800 --> 01:31:54.189
Do you think it's better
for me to go to jail

01:31:54.360 --> 01:31:56.396
or maybe let my family get killed?

01:31:56.560 --> 01:32:01.190
For Smokey who's already dead?
Ain't nothin' gonna bring him back.

01:32:01.360 --> 01:32:04.716
I'll stay out here free.
Maybe I can make some changes.

01:32:06.320 --> 01:32:09.073
Jerry, with this union rep job, man,

01:32:09.240 --> 01:32:12.710
it's a club in my hands.

01:32:13.600 --> 01:32:17.149
You're my friend, Jerry,
but you're thinking white.

01:32:19.160 --> 01:32:21.355
What the fuck does that mean?

01:32:21.520 --> 01:32:23.909
It means that you got
more chances than I got.

01:32:24.080 --> 01:32:28.676
You're always gonna have more chances.
I got one chance and I'm gonna take it.

01:32:28.840 --> 01:32:31.400
I'm black.
The police ain't gonna protect me.

01:32:31.560 --> 01:32:35.348
Six months after this thing's over,
I'll end up back where I started,

01:32:35.520 --> 01:32:38.159
living in some ghetto,
up to my black ass in bills,

01:32:38.320 --> 01:32:42.108
wondering what night they'll come in
and kill the kids, Caroline and me.

01:32:42.280 --> 01:32:45.795
If I gotta kiss ass,
I'm gonna pick the ass I'm gonna kiss.

01:32:45.960 --> 01:32:49.555
And it ain't gonna be the police,
cos they'll shit in my face.

01:32:49.720 --> 01:32:52.632
Was Smokey white?

01:32:52.800 --> 01:32:54.677
Man, you don't know the deal, do ya?

01:32:54.840 --> 01:32:57.912
You think I'm crazy?
You want revenge? You got a gun?

01:32:58.080 --> 01:33:00.799
You go out lookin' for killers
cos damn if I am.

01:33:03.080 --> 01:33:05.958
Look, man, at least this way,
inside the union,

01:33:06.120 --> 01:33:08.076
maybe I can make some changes.

01:33:08.240 --> 01:33:10.515
Fuck changes.

01:33:10.680 --> 01:33:13.433
Who are you kidding?

01:33:15.400 --> 01:33:19.359
The union gets the notebook,
you get promoted to a softjob.

01:33:19.520 --> 01:33:22.034
OK, you get the chance
to change things.

01:33:23.280 --> 01:33:26.272
But what do I get?
What about my family, Zeke?

01:33:26.440 --> 01:33:29.352
Why is your family
more important than my family?

01:33:29.520 --> 01:33:33.718
Jerry, there ain't nothin' in the worid
I wouldn't do

01:33:33.880 --> 01:33:35.757
to protect my babies and my wife.

01:33:36.960 --> 01:33:39.679
Now, you gotta take care
of your own family.

01:33:39.840 --> 01:33:42.718
You're a worker, man. I'm a worker.

01:33:42.880 --> 01:33:47.192
Let's work together. They need
a new foreman to take Miller's place.

01:33:47.360 --> 01:33:49.635
I can get you the job.

01:33:56.600 --> 01:33:58.670
I get screwed.

01:34:00.160 --> 01:34:02.116
That's all I know.

01:34:03.240 --> 01:34:05.629
You ought to think about it, man.

01:34:22.760 --> 01:34:25.513
- Hello, Bartowski.
- Hello.

01:34:27.200 --> 01:34:31.432
Well, the shit's really coming
down. I suppose you know that.

01:34:33.400 --> 01:34:37.359
The Detroit Police don't keep secrets
too well. This is a company town.

01:34:43.360 --> 01:34:47.592
Why didn't you call me sooner?
I could've prevented all this.

01:34:47.760 --> 01:34:49.512
I had nothing to do with that.

01:34:49.680 --> 01:34:53.593
You can still help us get the case
against the union. It's murder now.

01:34:57.240 --> 01:34:58.514
I got nothing to sell.

01:34:58.680 --> 01:35:02.559
I stole a notebook, heard conversations,
saw an industrial accident.

01:35:02.720 --> 01:35:05.518
Two guys can back me up.
One's dead, the other's a rep.

01:35:05.680 --> 01:35:09.468
Just tell us everything you know.
We'll piece it together.

01:35:15.400 --> 01:35:18.597
- What do I get out of it?
- A suspended sentence.

01:35:18.760 --> 01:35:20.751
How do I protect my family?

01:35:20.920 --> 01:35:23.673
You got no choice.
I'm the only friend you got.

01:35:23.840 --> 01:35:28.072
I'm the only one who can protect you
or your family.

01:35:28.240 --> 01:35:31.869
Maybe I'll go to Canada.
Can't be any worse there.

01:35:32.720 --> 01:35:35.518
They'll find you wherever you go.

01:35:35.680 --> 01:35:38.513
- I can take care of myself.
- Oh, yeah? Can you?

01:35:38.680 --> 01:35:42.753
Face it, you're one man, all alone,

01:35:42.920 --> 01:35:45.514
and your friends
aren't going to help you now.

01:35:55.240 --> 01:35:59.313
I won't help you, Burrows. I'll let them
kill me before I turn stoolie.

01:35:59.480 --> 01:36:02.631
Oh, yeah? Who are you kidding?

01:37:04.200 --> 01:37:08.352
I dedicate this drink
to all alcoholics at General Motors.

01:37:08.520 --> 01:37:10.909
How about a bourbon, Joe?

01:37:16.840 --> 01:37:19.434
How'd Zeke get to be rep?

01:37:19.600 --> 01:37:23.639
Yeah, they've got us these days, pal.

01:37:23.800 --> 01:37:26.917
He's sure enjoying it, that's for sure.

01:37:52.600 --> 01:37:53.999
<i>Operator</i>.

01:37:54.160 --> 01:37:56.720
I'd like to place a long-distance call,
collect.

01:37:56.880 --> 01:38:02.955
Area code 616-582-3976.

01:38:03.120 --> 01:38:06.032
<i>- Thank you. Who's calling?</i>
- Jerry Bartowski.

01:38:08.320 --> 01:38:09.309
<i>Hello?</i>

01:38:09.480 --> 01:38:12.472
<i>I have a call from Jerry Bartowski</i>.
<i>Will you accept charges?</i>

01:38:12.640 --> 01:38:13.629
<i>Yes</i>.

01:38:13.800 --> 01:38:17.031
- Arlene, it's me.
<i>- Turn that down, Debby. How are you?</i>

01:38:17.200 --> 01:38:19.668
- How are you?
<i>- Fine</i>.

01:38:19.840 --> 01:38:24.038
- Is there anything unusual?
<i>- Like what?</i>

01:38:24.200 --> 01:38:27.829
Salesmen, or guys hanging around,
or anything like that?

01:38:28.000 --> 01:38:30.719
<i>- No</i>.
- Where are the kids?

01:38:30.880 --> 01:38:35.192
<i>- They're here</i>.
- Listen, don't let them go out alone.

01:38:35.360 --> 01:38:38.591
<i>What's wrong, Jerry?</i>

01:38:38.760 --> 01:38:42.275
- I think they're following me.
- <i>Who?</i>

01:38:43.360 --> 01:38:46.636
I'm the only one left
that knows what went down.

01:38:46.800 --> 01:38:51.476
About the notebook, the loans,
Smokey's death, how Zeke got his job.

01:38:51.640 --> 01:38:53.471
Everything will be OK when I'm dead.

01:38:53.640 --> 01:38:57.679
- <i>Where are you now?</i>
- In the bar. I'm afraid to go home.

01:38:57.840 --> 01:39:00.718
<i>Call the police right now</i>.

01:39:00.880 --> 01:39:04.077
I'm not a brave man.
I can't take them all on alone.

01:39:04.240 --> 01:39:06.071
<i>Can't you get a job like Zeke did?</i>

01:39:06.240 --> 01:39:08.117
Yeah, but I don't trust them.

01:39:08.280 --> 01:39:11.556
<i>Just keep quiet</i>.
<i>Then won't they leave you alone?</i>

01:39:11.720 --> 01:39:13.790
I don't see how they can do that.

01:42:25.400 --> 01:42:27.038
- Don't move!
- Don't shoot.

01:42:27.200 --> 01:42:30.351
Get out of the car!

01:42:30.520 --> 01:42:32.476
I want... I wanna confess a robbery.

01:42:32.640 --> 01:42:34.471
You got to hear your rights first.

01:42:34.640 --> 01:42:37.791
I want to talk to an FBI man
named John Burrows.

01:42:37.960 --> 01:42:40.110
It's about a murder.

01:43:38.360 --> 01:43:42.273
Check the torque
on the steering gear bolt.

01:43:42.440 --> 01:43:44.476
Get these lines clipped.

01:43:45.800 --> 01:43:48.268
It needs rail car tie-ons.

01:43:50.720 --> 01:43:53.393
Keep this line movin'.
This ain't no floor show!

01:43:53.560 --> 01:43:56.074
That ain't nothing special to look at.

01:44:05.960 --> 01:44:08.713
Hey. Big man.

01:44:14.440 --> 01:44:16.954
Shithead's gonna sing like a bird.

01:44:17.120 --> 01:44:19.554
- The son of a bitch.
- Zeke's coming.

01:44:28.360 --> 01:44:30.828
Tell 'em I'm gonna turn it off downtown.

01:44:53.160 --> 01:44:55.913
Hey, scumbag.

01:44:56.080 --> 01:44:59.595
I'd sure hate to be living
in them pretty little white shoes.

01:44:59.760 --> 01:45:01.830
I see they finally fixed your locker.

01:45:02.000 --> 01:45:05.072
Nobody said you men could stop workin'.

01:45:05.240 --> 01:45:08.232
You'll see him in court.

01:45:08.400 --> 01:45:11.517
No, it's all right.
Let me talk to the new steward.

01:45:11.680 --> 01:45:14.877
Yeah, let him tell me
about how he likes the workin' man.

01:45:15.040 --> 01:45:17.508
You care about nothin'
but your own Polack ass.

01:45:17.680 --> 01:45:21.434
Hey, blood, you double-crossed me.
Tried to get me killed.

01:45:21.600 --> 01:45:25.070
I ain't your blood, motherfucker!
You do anything to stay out ofjail!

01:45:25.240 --> 01:45:26.878
Even sell out on your friends.

01:45:27.040 --> 01:45:29.076
I ain't the one that sold out, you are!

01:45:29.240 --> 01:45:31.151
Yeah, you jive honky?

01:45:31.320 --> 01:45:35.472
You ain't looking out for nobody but
number one. That's you, jive white boy!

01:45:35.640 --> 01:45:37.278
You ain't nothing, you nigger.

01:45:37.440 --> 01:45:40.477
I hope your parents protect your ass,
cos you'll have to hide!

01:45:40.640 --> 01:45:42.551
- Fucking nigger!
- Motherfucker!

01:45:42.720 --> 01:45:44.233
Kill him!

01:45:48.240 --> 01:45:51.789
<i>They pit lifers against new</i>
<i>boys, young against old,</i>

01:45:51.960 --> 01:45:57.114
<i>black against white. Everything</i>
<i>they do is to keep us in our place</i>.

